{% endraw %}

We'll loop through different parameter choices and plot the derived affinity matrix for each one, using the current affinity from flow function, which sets the affinity between $x_1$ and $x_2$, with $flow$ at $x_1$, as {% raw %} $$ \exp{(-\|x_2 - x_2\| + a|\|flow\|^2 - \langle flow , \|flow\| \frac{x_2 - x_1}{\|x_2 - x_1\|}\rangle)} $$ {% endraw %}

{% raw %} 
from directed_graphs.diffusion_flow_embedding import affinity_matrix_from_pointset_to_pointset
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import torch
sigmas = [0.2, 0.5] #[0.2, 0.5, 0.8, 1, 2, 5, 10, 15]
flow_strengths = [1, 2] #[1,2,4,8,12,16]
fig, axs = plt.subplots(len(sigmas),len(flow_strengths), figsize=(len(sigmas*6),len(flow_strengths)*6))
X = torch.tensor(X)
flow = torch.tensor(flow)
for i, s in enumerate(sigmas):
  for j, f in enumerate(flow_strengths):
    A = affinity_matrix_from_pointset_to_pointset(X, X, flow, sigma=s, flow_strength=f)
    A = A.numpy()
    axs[i][j].set_title(f"$\sigma = {s}$ and $f={f}$")
    axs[i][j].imshow(A)
plt.show()
